OL,3,CPassenger needs 'life-long care' after
OL,4,Cnitrous oxide-fuelled crash
OL,6,FOne of the passengers, 25-year-old
OL,7,FHarlan Moon from Billingham, requires
OL,8,Flife-long care for the injuries they
OL,9,Fsuffered during the crash.
OL,11,FThornton was charged with causing
OL,12,Fserious injury by dangerous driving
OL,13,Fand supplying a psychoactive substance.
OL,15,FHe appeared before Teesside Crown
OL,16,FCourt on Wednesday 4 September, where
OL,17,Fhe was sentenced to a total of three
OL,18,Fyears and 11 months in prison.
