OL,3,CPassenger needs 'life-long care' after
OL,4,Cnitrous oxide-fuelled crash
OL,6,FIn a victim impact statement read to
OL,7,Fthe court, Harlan's father Allan Moon
OL,8,Fsaid: "On 23rd October 2022 everything
OL,9,Fchanged for us and our family. Harlan
OL,10,Fnow requires 24/7 care and still is
OL,11,Fnot home.
OL,13,F"I see my son laid in hospital and
OL,14,Flooking at him, it's Harlan but I know
OL,15,Fthat it isn't my son that I knew
OL,16,Fbefore the collision. I struggle to
OL,17,Fcomprehend this and worry that I will
OL,18,Fnot get my son back."
OL,26,@pD@GOUuD@AOU
